{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:19:50.348433+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my examination of the repository, here are the findings:\n\n---\n\n## Package Manager: **Yarn**\n\nThe repository expects contributors to use **Yarn** as the package manager. Evidence:\n\n- **`yarn.lock`** file is present (lockfile specific to Yarn).\n- The `package.json` scripts section contains `\"fix\": \"yarn lint --fix\"` (explicitly invoking `yarn`).\n- The **`Taskfile.yaml`** task runner uses `yarn install` and `yarn release`.\n\n---\n\n## Environment-Specific Scripts\n\n### Environment Files (`envs/` directory)\n\n| File | Environment |\n|------|-------------|\n| `envs/.env.local` | Local development |\n| `envs/.env.stg` | Staging |\n| `envs/.env.prod` | Production |\n\n### Development Scripts\n\n| Script | Command | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `dev` | `cross-env NODE_ENV=local vite --host` | Start dev server (local env) |\n| `dev:stg` | `cross-env NODE_ENV=stg vite` | Start dev server (staging env) |\n\n### Build Scripts\n\n| Script | Command | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `build` | `vite build --mode prod` | Default production build |\n| `build:stg` | `cross-env vite build --mode test` | Staging/test build |\n| `build:prod` | `cross-env vite build --mode production` | Explicit production build |\n\n### Other Scripts\n\n| Script | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `serve` | Preview the built app (`vite preview --host`) |\n| `lint` | Run ESLint across the codebase |\n| `fix` | Auto-fix lint issues (`yarn lint --fix`) |\n| `deploy` | Deploy to GitHub Pages (`gh-pages -d dist`) |\n\nAdditionally, the **`Taskfile.yaml`** provides a `task init` command that sets up the project by installing global npm tools, copying `envs/.env.local` to `.env`, and running `yarn install`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 739, "prompt_tokens": 10467, "total_to